FBIS3-38607 "drweu024_j_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-024 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Feb 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Andreatta Hints at Sanctions LD0302202494 Rome RAI Uno Television Network in Italian 1900 GMT 3 Feb 94 LD0302202494 Rome RAI Uno Television Network Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] [Correspondent] Croatia, following the new Yugoslav federation, may now have sanctions imposed against it. [passage omitted] Foreign Minister Beniamino Andreatta said that he agreed with this. [passage omitted] [Begin Andreatta recording] Quite obviously, a Croatian offensive supported by forces from outside would have consequences -- that is economic reactions by the international community. The relationship between the EU [European Union] and Croatia would of course be affected. [end recording]
